title: Photos: Israel claims victory over Hamas in a key city as many in Gaza go hungry
description: In the past week, the U.S. has targeted Israeli settlers in the West Bank, families continued to mourn their losses and Israel claimed to have defeated Hamas in a key Gaza city.

title: Journalist Michele Norris reveals America's 'Hidden Conversations' about race
description: Norris wanted to see how Americans view race, so she asked people to share their thoughts in six words. Eventually, the project grew, garnering some 500,000 million entries from 100+ countries.

title: King Charles is being treated for cancer
description: King Charles III has been diagnosed with a form of cancer and began treatment Monday, Buckingham Palace says.

title: Up First briefing: Senate unveils immigration bill; rain, winds batter California
description: Bipartisan Senate negotiators release a $118 billion border bill. Storms leave hundreds of thousands of Californians without electricity.

title: Grammys 2024: 10 takeaways from music's biggest night (Taylor's version)
description: Miley Cyrus, SZA, Billie Eilish and others had a big night. But once again, the music industry found itself in the long shadow of Taylor Swift, who won album of the year and announced a new project.

title: Tracy Chapman's 'Fast Car' climbs the iTunes charts after her Grammy performance
description: Chapman has performed sparingly in recent years. She took the Grammy stage to raucous applause and capped her performance with Luke Combs by receiving a standing ovation.

title: Police raided George Pelecanos' home. 15 years later, he's ready to write about it
description: Crime fiction author and screenwriter George Pelecanos is known for his gritty realism. His latest short story collection takes that same unsparing look at his own past.

title: One year after the toxic train derailment, East Palestine is a town divided
description: The East Palestine community is divided and exhausted, with many residents ready to move forward, even as others continue to raise concerns about the air and water.

title: You can order a test to find out your biological age. Is it worth it?
description: Learning your DNA age sounds intriguing. But researchers caution the results might make you nervous. And they don't tell you much about what steps to take next.

title: Meet 'Dr. Tatiana,' the professor getting people on TikTok excited about physics
description: Videos of Tatiana Erukhimova's enthusiastic teaching style have gone viral on social media. The secret to her success? It didn't happen overnight.

title: Why problems at a key Boeing supplier may help explain the company's 737 Max 9 mess
description: Federal investigators are scrutinizing Spirit AeroSystems, a major Boeing supplier based in Kansas, as they try to understand why a fuselage panel blew off an Alaska Airlines jet in midair last month.

title: Tennessee law denied Allie Phillips an abortion. So she's now running for office
description: Phillips, 28, never expected to go into politics. But after she got devastating news about her pregnancy, everything changed.

title: Samsung chief Lee Jae-yong is acquitted of financial crimes related to 2015 merger
description: The ruling could ease the legal troubles for the Samsung heir less than two years after he was pardoned of bribing a former president in a scandal that toppled a previous South Korean government.

title: Photos: See how the atmospheric river is battering California
description: Forecasters now say 8 to 15 inches of rain could fall in the mountains and foothills of Southern California.

title: The 2026 World Cup final will take place at New Jersey's MetLife Stadium
description: The complex home to the New York Jets and Giants and located in East Rutherford, N.J., will be renamed the New York New Jersey Stadium during the July 19 final.
